tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/050-harness_adhere-task.log:1966:        "019db58b-b382-7060-afcd-73b9d68cd740"
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/050-harness_adhere-task.log:3436:        "body": "Every testable behavior has a stable `BEH-*` identifier that is referenced from: (1) the spec/plan behavior inventory, (2) the cucumber scenario via a `@BEH-*` tag, (3) mutation survivor triage records, and (4) coverage classification records. Behavior IDs are immutable once published; renames require an abandon+replace event pair in the orchestrator. A behavior claim without a resolvable `BEH-*` link in all four artifacts is treated as incomplete traceability and fails the final gate."
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/050-harness_adhere-task.log:3443:        "name": "coverage-behavior-first",
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/050-harness_adhere-task.log:3453:          "coverage"
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/050-harness_adhere-task.log:3456:        "body": "Coverage is interpreted as a behavior-gap signal, not a vanity percentage. The coverage artifact must classify uncovered paths into two buckets: (1) missing-behavior — code whose absence of coverage corresponds to a behavior without a scenario, which requires adding/extending a `.feature` scenario; and (2) dead/support code — code that is not itself a behavior claim, which requires removal or explicit support-classification. Raw line/branch totals are reported but never gate on their own."
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/050-harness_adhere-task.log:3514:      "description": "Import/sync Rust testing standards (BDD, mutation, coverage interpretation, no-skip, traceability) into active standards and bind relevance context for this spec.",
