tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/031-harness_do-task.log:970:tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260422T234402Z/commands/002-harness_adhere-task.log:1523:["tanren/standards/rust-testing/bdd-scenarios.md","tanren/standards/rust-testing/mutation-strength.md","tanren/standards/rust-testing/coverage-behavior-first.md","tanren/standards/rust-testing/no-skip-enforcement.md","tanren/standards/rust-testing/behavior-traceability.md","just check: exit 0"]
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/031-harness_do-task.log:973:tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260422T234402Z/commands/002-harness_adhere-task.log:1533:    \"tanren/standards/rust-testing/coverage-behavior-first.md\",
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/031-harness_do-task.log:981:tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260422T234402Z/commands/002-harness_adhere-task.log:1693:        "body": "Every testable behavior has a stable `BEH-*` identifier that is referenced from: (1) the spec/plan behavior inventory, (2) the cucumber scenario via a `@BEH-*` tag, (3) mutation survivor triage records, and (4) coverage classification records. Behavior IDs are immutable once published; renames require an abandon+replace event pair in the orchestrator. A behavior claim without a resolvable `BEH-*` link in all four artifacts is treated as incomplete traceability and fails the final gate."
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/031-harness_do-task.log:982:tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260422T234402Z/commands/002-harness_adhere-task.log:1700:        "name": "coverage-behavior-first",
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/031-harness_do-task.log:983:tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260422T234402Z/commands/002-harness_adhere-task.log:1710:          "coverage"
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/031-harness_do-task.log:984:tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260422T234402Z/commands/002-harness_adhere-task.log:1713:        "body": "Coverage is interpreted as a behavior-gap signal, not a vanity percentage. The coverage artifact must classify uncovered paths into two buckets: (1) missing-behavior — code whose absence of coverage corresponds to a behavior without a scenario, which requires adding/extending a `.feature` scenario; and (2) dead/support code — code that is not itself a behavior claim, which requires removal or explicit support-classification. Raw line/branch totals are reported but never gate on their own."
