tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/031-harness_do-task.log:1227:tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/007-harness_adhere-task.log:666:      "description": "Import/sync Rust testing standards (BDD, mutation, coverage interpretation, no-skip, traceability) into active standards and bind relevance context for this spec.",
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/031-harness_do-task.log:1231:tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/007-harness_adhere-task.log:728:      "description": "Introduce staged justfile/CI scaffolding commands for BDD, mutation, and coverage without turning final enforcement on yet, so iterative tasks remain demonstrable.",
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/031-harness_do-task.log:1232:tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/007-harness_adhere-task.log:733:          "measurable": "just targets for scenario/mutation/coverage scaffolding execute successfully."
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/031-harness_do-task.log:1247:tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/007-harness_adhere-task.log:1016:        "body": "Every testable behavior has a stable `BEH-*` identifier that is referenced from: (1) the spec/plan behavior inventory, (2) the cucumber scenario via a `@BEH-*` tag, (3) mutation survivor triage records, and (4) coverage classification records. Behavior IDs are immutable once published; renames require an abandon+replace event pair in the orchestrator. A behavior claim without a resolvable `BEH-*` link in all four artifacts is treated as incomplete traceability and fails the final gate."
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/031-harness_do-task.log:1248:tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/007-harness_adhere-task.log:1023:        "name": "coverage-behavior-first",
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/031-harness_do-task.log:1249:tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/007-harness_adhere-task.log:1033:          "coverage"
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/031-harness_do-task.log:1250:tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/007-harness_adhere-task.log:1036:        "body": "Coverage is interpreted as a behavior-gap signal, not a vanity percentage. The coverage artifact must classify uncovered paths into two buckets: (1) missing-behavior — code whose absence of coverage corresponds to a behavior without a scenario, which requires adding/extending a `.feature` scenario; and (2) dead/support code — code that is not itself a behavior claim, which requires removal or explicit support-classification. Raw line/branch totals are reported but never gate on their own."
